<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOUIS BONESIO JR.; RECEIVED ORGANS FROM DIFFERENT DONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Louis Bonesio Jr., 60, the world's first recipient of two vital organs from 
different donors. Bonesio received a heart from one donor in 1974 and a kidney 
from another in 1985.The heart transplant surgery was performed at Stanford 
University Medical Center and the kidney transplant at UC San Francisco. Other 
multiple organ transplants have involved single donors. Bonesio was praised by 
medical personnel for his positive attitude and sense of humor, joking with 
doctors after the first transplant that he had "a 16-year-old heart and 40 
years of experience." He asked doctors to give him a new kidney, saying 
dialysis kept him from enjoying his life and community volunteer work. On Feb. 
6 in Gilroy, Calif., of heart failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
