 Norman Del Mar, 74, British conductor and author who focused on works of Sir 
Edward Elgar, Gustav Mahler and Richard Strauss.Del Mar began his career as a 
horn player with the Royal Philharmonic and became an assistant to conductor 
Sir Thomas Beecham. He made his debut as a conductor in 1947. He led many 
