<TEXT>
<P>
 Judge Dismisses Insider Trading Charges: A federal judge in New York has 
dismissed civil charges brought by the Securities and Exchange Commission 
against two stockbrokers, Frank Petrone and James Zanengo.In an oral ruling 
from the bench, U.S. District Judge Loretta A. Preska threw out the charges 
Feb. 4 after a five-day trial, a lawyer for Petrone said. The SEC had accused 
the two of trading on inside information in the Philip Morris takeover of Kraft 
in 1988. Lawyer Jody M. Peikin said the judge stated she found no evidence of 
them receiving illegal inside information. 
