<P>
 Survey Shows Baby Boomers Seeking Security: More than 70% of Americans say the 
would sacrifice new cars, brand name goods and going out to restaurants to 
ensure a financially secure retirement, according to a recent survey. More than 
60% of baby boomers -- Americans between the ages 29 and 47 -- say they will 
not have enough for retirement no matter how much they save, according to a 
report commissioned by the Municipal Bond Investors Assurance Corp. About 66% 
of baby boomers say they believe their retirement savings are at risk. 
