PACIFIC WATCH: AUSTRALIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jobless Rate Declines: Unemployment in January fell to its lowest level in 20 
months, and employment rose for a fifth consecutive month, confirming that the 
nation's economic recovery is gaining steam, analysts said.The January jobless 
rate fell 0.1% to 10.6%. Economists had forecast a rise in unemployment. 
Employment grew by 22,000 jobs in January. The decrease in unemployment was 
achieved even though more people were out looking for work. The participation 
rate, which measures the number of people in jobs and those looking for work, 
increased 0.1% to 63.1%. 
