IN BRIEF; MATURE DRIVER PROGRAM CAN CUT INSURANCE COST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Responsible Driver Course Home Study Edition for people age 55 and over 
with good driving records is available from the Department of Motor Vehicles in 
Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 By reading the illustrated study book and completing a quiz, drivers may 
receive the DMV California Mature Driver Improvement Certificate.The 
certificate can be submitted to your insurance company for a 5% or larger auto 
insurance discount good for three years. Individuals should check with their 
insurance carrier to determine eligibility and discount amount. For additional 
information on the Responsible Driver Course Home Study Edition, call (800) 
233-0226. 
</P>
<P>
 The course costs $21 per person. To enroll, send check or money order for $21 
per person to Responsible Driver Course and mail with your name and address to: 
P.O. Box 109-H, Whittier, Calif. 90608. 
</P>
