<P>
IN BRIEF; LECTURE TO RECOUNT SKIERS' HEROIC EXPLOITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The actions of Norwegian skiers who prevented Adolf Hitler from developing an 
atomic bomb will be chronicled in "Skis Against the Bomb" on Wednesday at 7 
p.m. at the Mark Taper Auditorium of the Central Library, at 5th and Flower 
streets in Downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The free lecture and slide show will be presented by Trond Woxen, a theater 
director, writer and former nuclear/biological/chemical warfare specialist in 
the Norwegian army. 
</P>
<P>
 Woxen will discuss the adventure of the team who skied to the remote Norsk 
Hydro Plant in Rjukan, Norway, and blew up the facility, being used by Hitler 
to develop an atomic bomb during World War II.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Louise Steinman at (213) 228-7472. 
