<HEADLINE>
<P>
118 FREEWAY CONNECTOR REOPENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Simi Valley (118) Freeway connection to the San Diego (405) and Foothill 
(210) freeways, which was closed after the Northridge earthquake, was reopened 
Sunday, Caltrans officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, most of the transition roads linking the three freeways were 
opened Sunday, meaning that commuters will now be able to switch from freeway 
to freeway without taking as many surface streets, a Caltrans spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 118 Freeway west of the 405 is still closed in both directions, the 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 A section of the Golden State Freeway between Lyons Avenue in Newhall and 
Roxford Street in Sylmar will be closed overnight and Tuesday for quake-related 
repairs, from 11:30 p.m. until 5 a.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
