<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAMILY IDENTIFIES TEEN WHO FATALLY SHOT SELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Relatives of a 16-year-old boy who fatally shot himself in the head while 
playing with a gun identified the victim Sunday as Ismael Dominguez. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the Santa Ana teen-ager was playing with the loaded handgun at his 
home on Bishop Street Saturday when he shot himself.Dominguez had been showing 
the weapon to a friend who apparently warned him against playing with it, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 When the friend, Javier Paramo, 20, of Santa Ana, left the room, he heard a 
gunshot and returned to find his friend with a fatal wound, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two women who were in the house at the time of the shooting verified Paramo's 
story, police and Dominguez's relatives said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Dominguez's parents live in Mexico, police said, and he was staying with 
relatives. 
</P>
