<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Baxter Healthcare Corp.: An Irvine-based subsidiary announced last week that 
it has bought a Brazilian manufacturer of heart valves. 
</P>
<P>
 Baxter's Bentley division acquired Macchi Engenharia Biomedica Ltda., based in 
Sao Paulo.Macchi makes blood oxygenators and mechanical heart valves and 
distributes pacemakers. Financial terms of the transaction were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Bentley also said it has signed a new four-year agreement with Haemonetics 
Corp. of Braintree, Mass., to continue distributing Haemonetics' surgical 
blood-salvage products in the United States. The automated systems are used to 
collect patients' blood before, during and after surgery for re-infusion to the 
patient. 
</P>
<P>
 Baxter Healthcare Corp. is the main unit of Baxter International Inc. in 
Deerfield, Ill., the world's leading maker of health care products. Bentley 
makes disposable oxygenators, which provide oxygen to the blood while the heart 
and lungs are stopped during open-heart surgery. 
</P>
