<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; DEFENSEMAN OZOLINSH GIVES SHARKS VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sandis Ozolinsh scored with 1:59 remaining to give the San Jose Sharks a 1-0 
victory over the Chicago Blackhawks on Sunday at San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
 Ozolinsh was too deep in the offensive zone and not in good position to get 
back on defense when he took a pass from Johan Garpenlov and scored the winner. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was in the wrong place at the right time," the defenseman said with a grin. 
</P>
<P>
 Florida 2, Vancouver 1 -- Brian Benning and Bob Kudelski scored power-play 
goals and Mark Fitzpatrick made 33 saves for the Panthers at Miami. 
</P>
<P>
 New Jersey 3, Tampa Bay 3 -- Bernie Nichols, formerly of the Kings, scored two 
goals for the Devils at St. Petersburg, Fla., and became the 39th player in NHL 
history to reach 1,000 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Pittsburgh 3, Philadelphia 0 -- Mario Lemieux, in his second game since 
returning from back problems, scored two goals and goaltender Tom Barrasso 
recorded his 20th shutout at Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
 Dallas 5, Buffalo 3 -- Mike Modano scored two goals at Buffalo, N.Y., leading 
the Stars to their sixth straight road victory. 
</P>
