<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; BECKER'S SERVE HELPS HIM GET PAST KORDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Defending champion Boris Becker used one of his greatest weapons -- an 
overpowering serve -- to break a one-year drought with a 6-2, 3-6, 6-3 victory 
over Petr Korda of the Czech Republic that gave the German the Muratti Time 
indoor title Sunday at Milan, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Todd Martin defeated Brad Gilbert, 6-4, 7-5, in the final of the 
Kroger-St.Jude International tournament Sunday at Memphis, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin, ranked ninth in the world, won his first title last May at Coral 
Springs, Fla., and then lost in four finals, including the Australian Open last 
month where he was defeated by Pete Sampras. Martin earned $110,500 Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Natalia Zvereva of Belarus won the Virginia Slims of Chicago with a 6-3, 7-5 
victory over Chanda Rubin. Zvereva, 22, used a steady serve and a variety of 
shots, including a low-to-the ground slice backhand to offset the hard ground 
strokes of Rubin, 17. 
</P>
