<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITANS, CS NORTHRIDGE SPLIT IN SOFTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jennifer Mortensen pitched a seven-hitter to help Cal State Fullerton to a 1-0 
victory over Cal State Northridge in a nonconference women's softball game 
Sunday at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge, ranked No. 3 in the nation, came back to score four runs in the 
13th to take the second game, 4-0. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second shutout of the season for Mortensen (2-0). She had four 
strikeouts. The 16th-ranked Titans scored in the fifth when Heidi Robertson 
singled, stole second, was sacrificed to third and scored on a throwing error. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (2-2) made four consecutive errors in the 13th to lead to all four 
Cal State Northridge runs. The Titans had six errors in the game. Northridge is 
1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In Pacific 10 wrestling: 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno State 26, Cal State Fullerton 6 -- Christian Holiday (158 pounds) and 
Laszlo Molner (167) were the only winners for the host Titans. Holiday beat 
Keith Richards, 3-2. Molner beat Eddie Luna, 18-5. 
</P>
<P>
 Sam Lopez of Fresno beat Kevin Mabry, 20-8, at 118 pounds. Lopez was an 
All-American at Cypress College. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Hawaii 78, Cal State Fullerton 61 -- Jenny Kaeo scored 21 points and teammate 
Melanie Azmaa had 15 for visiting Hawaii (17-3, 10-2). Shayla Bradshaw had 18 
for Cal State Fullerton (2-18, 1-11). 
</P>
