EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; CITY TO CONSIDER REZONING REQUEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura City Council today will consider a developer's request to rezone 
an area designated for office space to allow residential housing. 
</P>
<P>
 The five-acre parcel is on Thille Street between Hill Road and Partridge 
Avenue on the city's east end. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills-based Raznick & Sons wants to build a 100-unit apartment 
project on the vacant site instead of the seven-building office complex it had 
originally planned. 
</P>
<P>
 City staff is recommending against the zone change. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're going to be short of office space in the future," Community Development 
Director Everett Millais said, "and we've got all the residential housing we 
can handle." PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
