ROBBERS KILL 3 IN MISSOURI CONVENIENCE STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three convenience store employees were shot to death during a robbery, police 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of Fred Jones, 58, was found in a walk-in cooler at Casey's General 
Store around 1 a.m. The bodies of Mary Bratcher, 46, and Mabel A. Scruggs, 57, 
were found in a restroom. 
</P>
<P>
 All three had been shot in the head. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they did not know how much money was taken. 
</P>
