 Bratcher, the store's manager, had apparently gone to the store Saturday night 
to help close up. Neither Jones, a new employee, nor Scruggs was familiar with 
the closing routine, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 There are no security cameras in the store, and the alarm system had not been 
activated, Deputy Police Chief Carroll Highbarger said. 
