<P>
 "Teachers' Lounge" has set a new Laguna Playhouse attendance record for a 
non-musical production. Playhouse executive director Richard Stein says John 
Twomey's original comedy was seen by roughly 11,000 playgoers, or 96% capacity 
for the entire run (Jan. 11-Feb. 6). The previous record-holder was 
Shakespeare's "A Midsummer Night's Dream." 
